name: Communication Building, Boise State campus
street: Theater Lane between Albertsons Library and the tennis courts
directions:
There are TWO gender-neutral bathrooms in the comm building. One is on the first floor. Go in through the main entrance and hang a left. It’s right there. 
There is also a gender-neutral bathroom on the second floor. There is an elevator in the building so it’s fully accessible. If walking, go through the main door to the comm building. Turn left and go up the stairs. It’s on your left.
comment: Treat these restrooms with respect. This building is a university treasure and was the first student union at BSU. Most of the folks who work in the comm Dept are pretty cool. Good place to go.
